# HTML/CSS Structure and Styling Rules

## HTML Structure Standards
Follow the established patterns from [index.html](mdc:index.html) and course pages:

### Page Structure
- Use semantic HTML5 structure with proper meta tags
- Include responsive viewport meta tag
- Use consistent title naming: `[Course]-[Module]-[Day]-[Description]`

### Loading and Presentation Integration
- Include loading spinner with fade-in effects for embedded content
- Use iframe for Gamma presentations with proper sandbox attributes
- Implement responsive design with mobile-first approach

### CSS Guidelines
- Use CSS custom properties for consistent theming
- Follow the established color scheme: `#667eea` to `#764ba2` gradient
- Implement smooth transitions and hover effects
- Use flexbox and grid for layout

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach with breakpoints at 768px and 480px
- Use `100vh` and `100dvh` for proper mobile viewport handling
- Ensure touch-friendly interface elements

### Performance Considerations
- Use `loading="lazy"` for iframes
- Implement proper loading states
- Optimize animations for smooth performance

### Accessibility
- Include proper ARIA labels and titles
- Ensure keyboard navigation support
- Maintain sufficient color contrast ratios

## Code Examples
```css
/* Standard loading spinner */
.spinner {
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  border: 4px solid #f3f3f3;
  border-top: 4px solid #667eea;
  border-radius: 50%;
  animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
}

/* Responsive iframe */
iframe {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100vh;
  height: 100dvh; /* Dynamic viewport height for mobile */
  border: none;
}
```